description: For sale: $269,900. Incredible opportunity to own a completely renovated unit at Summit House in Loring Park! This unit features a brand new kitchen with stainless steel refrigerator and range, new tile backsplash, new bathroom with updated tiling, re-finished wood flooring, new lighting, updated electrical panel, fresh paint throughout, new carpet, and IN-UNIT WASHER AND DRYER (very rare in these units)! Beautiful open concept layout and a private balcony. All utilities are included in the HOA fee, (including cable and internet). Summit House offers a variety of amenities including a party room, a workout facility, and free washer and dryer on every floor. You will enjoy the incredible rooftop pool and the view it offers! Premium location within walking distance from the Walker Art Center, restaurants, breweries, parks, and nightlife/entertainment! Convenient access to both downtown and uptown, this unit is a must see!

description: For sale: $219,900. Lowry Hill/Kenwood neighborhood. Walk to restaurants, bars, Walker Art Center, Downtown, Uptown, Lake of the Isles, public transit & more!. Across from Thomas Lowry Park.  Spacious/updated kitchen with quartz countertops & stainless steel appliances. 3 walk-in closets. 2nd bedroom has private entrance! Great light from West facing windows overlooking community patio. Storage/Laundry room in unit has hook up/is plumbed (requires a vent-less dryer) and/or there are multiple free laundry machines on each floor. Secure building offers a private courtyard space, great party room, and an onsite/live in manager. Heated underground garage parking space #G39 included in HOA. Building is very pet friendly. HOA includes Heating, Sanitation, Snow/Lawn Care, Snow Removal, Lawn Care, Outside Maintenance, Hazard Insurance, Basic Cable, Internet, Water/Sewer, Building Exterior, Professional Management, shared amenities, parking space! Rentals allowed with 12+ mo lease. No FHA. Quick move in possible.

description: For sale: $289,900. Come and Check out this chic, hip, & urban ground-level mansion unit. Nestled on the hill in this wonderfully positioned neighborhood close to Uptown, Downtown, Kenwood & Loring Park, This condo boasts with architectural details, nuances, & flavor throughout. The open concept floor plan floods with light from all of the large windows throughout the home. Attention to detail is evident everywhere there are many beautiful curved archways, roman columns, french doors, and custom-shaped windows. The kitchen has been updated w/granite countertops, a center island, & two-tone cabinets. There are two large updated baths with a  jacuzzi tub. Site landscaping is lovely & patio area just outside the door is private & inviting. One assigned outdoor and parking and a 2nd communal parking space are often available although not dedicated.

description: For sale: $129,000. Studio Condo in the Lowry Hill/Kenwood neighborhood.  Close to parks and museum.  Stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, wood flooring, heated/covered parking, and free laundry on every floor.  The building is secure, offers a private courtyard space, and an onsite/live in manager.  Quick move in available.  Building is pet friendly.  Unit is clean and vacant.  Special showing instructions given to agents to maintain a safe and sanitary environment.

For sale: $449,000. This immaculate and thoughtfully updated 2 bed + den 2 bath first floor unit in the boutique 301 Clifton building is sure to impress! Gorgeous finishes include brand new flooring, updated modern LED lighting with IP control, huge center island granite kitchen with new glass tile backsplash, Kenmore Elite fridge and dishwasher, soaring 12+ foot ceilings and fresh paint in neutral tones throughout, sleek gas fireplace with granite surround and custom IP/remote controlled window shades in living room with UV protection on windows and patio doors, 20x10 stamped concrete patio with access from living room and owner's bedroom. Ultra spacious owner's suite features an incredible custom built full wall unit with integrated electrical/lighting, storage system and two desk spaces; new custom closets installed in front entry, guest bed and owner's walk-in closet with usable floor to ceiling space. Unbeatable walk-ability to Loring Park, Uptown, Downtown and super easy 35/94/394 access. Don't miss the commanding 360 degree views from the rooftop deck overlooking the Downtown Minneapolis skyline and basilica!

description: For sale: $1,195,000. Don't miss this grand Victorian cornerstone brick home in Lowry Hill! Original charm with today's amenities. Beautiful hardwood floors, leaded glass, box beam ceilings, built ins, recently updated kitchen and grand staircase. Private third level master suite includes a spacious sitting area, updated full bathroom and walk-in closet. Four additional bedrooms and an office on second level.  The lower level includes a private one bedroom apartment with direct entrance to street. Spacious two story carriage house makes a great theater room, home office, and bonus room. Wonderful exterior spaces include the front porch, upper level balcony, Enjoy the 1,500 square foot rooftop deck above the 4+ car heated garage, and private backyard garden. Incredible value! Convenient location in Lowry Hill. Minutes to downtown Minneapolis, Uptown, City Lakes, parks and more.

For sale: $309,900. Beautiful 2 bedroom, 2 full bath. Pet friendly building. Laminate flooring throughout. Den could be closed off for 3rd sleeping area. Present building amenity upgrades including outdoor pool area which also has fabulous views of downtown Minneapolis. See today! Fast close possible.

description: For sale: $119,900. #Lowry Hill - Beautifully updated MN Brownstone.  Newer updated kitchen & Bath!  Prime Location!  Close to Art Center, Uptown, Lakes, Trails, Restaurants and so much more!  Pet friendly - Nice Park w/benches & walking paths right outside!  Low HOA dues. All in One Washer/Dryer in Unit!  Urban Living at its Best!  Hurry!  This one will go fast!

For sale: $749,900. This incredible east-facing Lowry Hill duplex is only one block to Kenwood Park and two blocks to Lake of the Isles! Each unit has 3 bedrooms, 2 baths and 2 garage stalls, hardwood flooring, wood-burning fireplace in living rooms, spacious eat-in kitchens, separate dining room, full tiled main floor bathrooms, two ultra spacious main floor bedrooms with large closets, both lower level bedrooms are a suite with 3/4 bath and walk-in closet. Each unit has its own free laundry and storage. This corner lot side by side duplex is rare for this area with stable rents; currently both units are rented. Wonderful investment or owner/occupant property.

For sale: $474,900. Welcome to the Groveland!  This meticulous 2 bedroom, 2 bath condo has one of the best locations on the Groveland Ave side of the building with tree lined streets and city views from the 5th floor.  Highlights include 9-ft ceilings, big windows, Brazilian Cherry floors, maple cabinetry, HUGE center island, granite counter tops, stainless appliances, gas fireplace, Private owners suite w/ spa bath and walk-in closet, generous dining with room to expand when entertaining larger groups, separate laundry and bonus storage/pantry room with built-in cabinetry.  Plus..2-heated garage stalls & extra storage right by the elevator.  Built w/concrete construction for quiet living, lovely building amenities, on-site property manager & the assoc fees includes about everything but electrical.  Gas grill included!   Walk to Loring Park, Uptown, Downtown, The Walker, Sculpture Garden and tons shops & restaurants. Your city awaits....

description:
For sale: $164,900. Rare Groveland Terrace unit for sale. 

Contract for Deed w/ $0 down is possible for the right applicant.

There is very little owner turnover in this development, only a few sold all year. Don't miss your chance to live at the best location in the city.

Wonderful location, walk to DT or city lakes. Freshly painted, neutral decor; loft-like feel. Spectacular DT views from shared terrace,  outdoor pool and grilling patio.

Granite countertops
SS Appliances
Custom Blinds
Two Custom Closets

Perfectly located in the desirable Lowry Hill Neighborhood. Easy walk to downtown, shopping, restaurants and coffee.

Perfect for the busy professional who wants easy access to the downtown and uptown social scene.

HOA fees cover high speed internet and HD cable package.

I've lived here for three years and the only reason I'm selling is because I want to live closer to my brother who is in Chaska.

Owner is an agent with Bridge Realty.

description: For sale: $1,295,000. Rarely available luxury Lowry Hill end-unit townhome. Enjoy this spectacular home on a private wooded urban setting with sweeping views of the Minneapolis skyline. Well-appointed design and open spaces with soaring ceilings. Two story arched windows in main level living room allows natural light to flow throughout this stunning space. Recently refreshed kitchen is spacious and bright. The informal dining room and sunroom with its walls and ceiling of windows offers a unique openness with unparalleled views. Two bedroom suites up with an open loft office. Private third level master suite with sitting area, balcony, full bathroom, and walk in closet. The finished walkout lower level offers a family room, exercise room, guest room and  bath. Walk out to private and generous side yard and patios. Three separate outdoor spaces allows you to enjoy the beautiful and private surroundings. Minutes to downtown. This home is perfect for entertaining or everyday living.

description: For sale: $88,900. Quaint and historic (1915) condo in the heart of Minneapolis 2 blocks from Franklin (Uptown) and a few blocks to downtown. Tall ceilings, oak and maple flooring. Great location, there is a park nearby, bus lines, plenty of restaurants and shops. In-building laundry and storage unit. Cat or small dog (under 40 pounds) OK. Located on first floor but the way they built these it's actually above ground a half floor. Huge windows. HOA $400. Great rental investment in an up and coming area. Renter has been in for 3 years at $920 per month, pays for itself. Taxes cheap. Please note bathroom is not red (painted white) and bedroom is not green (painted neutral gray). Ideally want to work with independent and cash buyers, but would consider 2.5% buyer realtor commission for the right buyer. This is a FSBO, please do not contact us if you are looking to list the property or have some other "business model" you are looking to advance. There is nothing wrong with the property. Seller's Alt disclosure available upon request.

description: For sale: $1,095,000. Welcome to 1918 Humboldt!  An elegant 5BR/5BA home on a fabulous block in Lowry Hill. Fantastic location in the heart of Lowry Hill near Kenwood Park, Lake of the Isles, restaurants, and shopping; and easy access to downtown, uptown, and freeways.

description:
For sale: $164,900. Rare Groveland Terrace unit for sale. 

Contract for Deed w/ $0 down is possible for the right applicant.

There is very little owner turnover in this development, only a few sold all year. Don't miss your chance to live at the best location in the city.

Wonderful location, walk to DT or city lakes. Freshly painted, neutral decor; loft-like feel. Spectacular DT views from shared terrace,  outdoor pool and grilling patio.

Granite countertops
SS Appliances
Custom Blinds
Two Custom Closets

Perfectly located in the desirable Lowry Hill Neighborhood. Easy walk to downtown, shopping, restaurants and coffee.

Perfect for the busy professional who wants easy access to the downtown and uptown social scene.

HOA fees cover high speed internet and HD cable package.

I've lived here for three years and the only reason I'm selling is because I want to live closer to my brother who is in Chaska.

Owner is an agent with Bridge Realty.

Recently sold: $211,000. Incredible 15th floor Summit House corner unit with unobstructed downtown skyline views from the private balcony. Both spacious bedrooms offer unobstructed views to the West overlooking the Basilica. Stunning bath finishes, built-in shelves and new stainless appliances are just some of the highlights of this very well appointed condo. Summit House also features several amenities including rooftop pools and cabanas, community rooms, shared laundry on each floor, fitness center, 24 hour security staff as well as underground heated parking and storage. Located steps from everything Loring Park has to offer. Schedule your private showing soon before this hits the market!

description: For sale: $169,900. Enjoy a quiet, private, green view within walking distance to The Walker Art Museum, Sculpture Garden, P.S. Steak, and Mass Transit. description: Recently sold: $370,000.

Recently sold: $273,200. Unique two-level condo in converted mansion in Lowry Hill! The sunny living room has a skylight, hardwood flooring, and a wood-burning fireplace. A curved wall opens to the dining room, complete with a wall that includes a wet bar and ample storage and countertop space. Imagine this area used while entertaining--set up your bar and buffet! 

The bedrooms are located on opposite sides of the living and dining rooms for privacy. The larger bedroom has a wonderful architectural window and a walk-in closet.

The kitchen is large enough to accommodate a table and chairs or a center-island for additional working and storage space. Updated appliances, hardwood floors, and a skylight all add to the ambiance of this room.

Outdoor spaces include a deck and an open porch. Catch some rays on the upper deck; dine on the open porch that provides shaded comfort.

This Lowry Hill location provides easy access to Lake of the Isles, downtown and Uptown Minneapolis, the Walker Art Center, the Sculpture Garden, and numerous restaurants, shops, and theaters.
